cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CYBER, cs.IR

This paper combines semantic and machine learning techniques to analyze population health risks. The use of an ontology and knowledge graph suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The development of a supervised cadre model also supports these categories. The use of a knowledge graph also suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) for managing and securing the data. Finally, the mention of provenance and documentation suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) for tracking and organizing the data and results.
